      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is the price of a commercial pizza oven in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Commercial pizza oven prices in India range from ₹60,000 for a basic single-deck gas oven to over ₹8 lakh for a high-capacity electric conveyor oven. Wood-fired ovens from Indian makers cost ₹80,000–₹2,80,000; Italian-made wood-fired ovens cost ₹2.5 lakh to ₹5 lakh+. Gas deck ovens for pizzerias range from ₹60,000 to ₹3.5 lakh. Electric conveyor ovens for QSR operations range from ₹1.5 lakh to ₹8 lakh. See the full price table at the top of this guide.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Which is better for a pizzeria in India — wood-fired or gas oven? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">It depends on your positioning and operations. Wood-fired ovens produce better Neapolitan pizza and have strong front-of-house appeal — ideal for premium pizzerias and standalone Italian restaurants. However, they require significant ventilation infrastructure, have regulatory complexity in some cities, and need skilled operators. Gas deck ovens are more practical: faster to set up, no smoke/ventilation issues, easier to operate consistently, and still produce excellent pizza. For a new standalone pizzeria doing New York or thin-crust style pizza, a gas deck oven is the more practical choice. For a premium Neapolitan concept, the wood-fired oven is worth the investment.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What temperature does a commercial pizza oven need to reach? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">It depends on the pizza style. Neapolitan pizza requires 430–480°C floor temperature and cooks in 60–90 seconds — achievable only in a wood-fired oven or top-of-range gas deck oven. New York thin-crust requires 300–350°C and cooks in 4–7 minutes — any quality gas or electric deck oven handles this. Standard QSR-style pizza cooks at 230–280°C in 8–15 minutes — conveyor ovens run in this range. Always verify that any oven you're considering can reach and maintain the temperature your pizza style requires.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is an electric or gas pizza oven better for a cloud kitchen in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For most cloud kitchens, an electric deck oven or electric conveyor oven is the better choice. Cloud kitchens are typically in shared commercial kitchen buildings where getting a new gas connection or installing a wood-burning chimney is impractical. Electric ovens are easier to install (just a 3-phase electrical connection), have no smoke issues, and offer excellent temperature control. If you already have PNG supply in the building, a gas deck oven is a strong option and slightly cheaper to run than electricity. Avoid LPG cylinders as your primary fuel for a cloud kitchen operation — the logistics and cost are unfavourable for daily use.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is a good pizza oven for a startup pizzeria in India on a tight budget? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For a startup pizzeria with a budget of ₹1–₹2 lakh, a single-deck or double-deck gas oven from a quality Indian manufacturer is the right starting point. Brands to consider: Genius Baking Equipment, Ekon, and other established Delhi NCR or Mumbai-based commercial kitchen equipment makers. Verify that the oven can reach at least 350°C (for thin-crust style) or 400°C+ (for closer-to-Neapolitan style). Avoid very cheap unbranded ovens — the temperature inconsistency will hurt product quality more than you save on capital cost. A quality Indian gas deck oven in the ₹85,000–₹1,40,000 range is a solid starter platform.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Do I need a special permit for a wood-fired pizza oven in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Requirements vary by city and state, but generally: you need your standard FSSAI license and fire safety NOC for any commercial kitchen. For wood-burning equipment specifically, some municipal corporations (particularly Delhi and Mumbai) have additional requirements or restrictions under local air quality and fire safety regulations. Before investing in a wood-fired oven, verify with your local municipal office and FSSAI inspector that wood-burning commercial kitchen equipment is permitted at your specific location. In most tier-2 cities and standalone buildings, there are no additional restrictions. In high-rise commercial buildings or dense urban areas, there may be restrictions on chimney routing and wood-burning fuel.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

